name: Neil Jary
oneLineSummary: An experienced software engineer and back-end Java developer
summary: An experienced and skilled developer with proven expertise in using new frameworks, tools and techniques to deliver improvements throughout the development life-cycle. Having extensive experience in the financial services and banking industry along with exceptional analytical and problem-solving skills. Working mainly in development roles, but also capable of operating in a support role when required. Excellent communications skills and able to bridge the gap between business users and technical team members. Looking for a senior development role in a progressive environment where I can continue to develop new skills and gain more knowledge of the latest development tools and techniques.

skills.notes: Neil has spent 30+ years working in software development exclusively in the banking and finance sector. During that time, he has acquired many technical skills as well as many business and project skills. His main focus over the years has been server-side development, more recently in the Java space with web services and micro-service. He also has some experience of developing front-end applications.

employment.notes: Neil has worked for a number of software houses and Westpac Bank before joining his current employer Landbay. He has held many positions on software development projects from Junior Programmer up to Project Manager and Principal Software Engineer.

notes: Since joining Landbay, Neil has worked on a number of projects concentrating on the back-end micro-services. These services are written in Java using Spring Boot as a framework and deployed to AWS.

roles.title: Principal Software Engineer
notes: Involved in the initial design and build of a new micro-service to execute decisions for a number of business contexts.

roles.title: Principal Software Engineer
notes: Working as a back-end engineer to automate the credit-checking process by building an interface to Equifax and processing, storing and displaying the results.

Since joining Westpac in the Institutional Banking (WIB) division, Neil has worked both in the FX & Commodities and Debt Markets departments. This has included working on custom enhancements to both Calypso and ION as well as a number of integration projects and bespoke developments.

Neil has worked both in teams and as a lone developer on a number of projects at Westpac. Most projects more recently have been run in an agile manner with short delivery cycles. All development work has been undertaken with a test-driven approach (TDD) using a number of dev ops tools including Jira and Bamboo.

roles.title: Principal Technical Lead Debt Markets
notes:
Cassandra Proof  of Concept
This project was to develop a proof of concept data hub using Cassandra (a no-SQL database) to see if it was suitable for more extensive use. A series of data source to Cassandra adaptors were developed to extract data from various relational databases and flat-file extracts and store the data in Cassandra. The data in Cassandra was then made available via a Rabbit MQ publisher in a spreadsheet plug-in.

Technologies: Java, Spring-Integration, Spring-Cassandra, Spring-JDBC, Spring-Batch, Spring-RabbitMQ.

Web-Based Data Viewer
Initially developed as a means of allowing users to view ION data according to user-defined templates that allowed selection of ION data-types, columns, record selection, sorting, grouping and formatting. The web interface also provided a means of populating spreadsheets according to templates based on the data in the viewer. The data displayed in the web-viewer was real-time with updates from ION highlighted to the user.

Technologies: HTML5, CSS, JavaScript, Bootstrap, Angular JS, Stomp, Java,Spring-MVC, web-sockets.

roles.title: Senior Technical Lead Debt Markets
notes:
Sales Portal iPad Application
In order to assist sales personnel in remote locations an iPad app was developed that could price configurable hedging scenarios and present the results in a graphical format to the clients. The application front-end was developed as a hybrid HTML5 application that was converted to an iPad app using the Phonegap (Apache Cordova) package. The back-end connected to Murex using a web-service layer to retrieve accurate pricing information.

Technologies: HTML5, CSS, JavaScript, Bootstrap, Spring-MVC, Java, Spring-Web-Services.

roles.title: Senior Java Developer Debt Markets
notes:
Murex-ION STP Integration
In Debt Markets, Murex is the system of record for all bond trading. ION is used for price publication and as a portal for trade requests received from TradeWeb, MarketAxxess and YieldBroker. This project was to develop a 2-way integration to keep Murex and ION in trade and position information in step with each other. This also included a web-based STP trade monitor and an automatic position reconciliation and notification process. This was primarily a server-side function written using Spring Integration with JMS links to Tibco to handle the trade message traffic.

Technologies: Java, Spring-Integration, Spring-Batch, Spring-MVC, GWT, Comet.

ION Credit Limit Checker
In order to provide traders using ION with accurate credit limits, a link to the Credient limits system was developed to allow either a batch or on-demand credit limit to be requested. This was primarily a server-side function written using Spring with JMS links to Tibco to handle the credit limit request and response message traffic.

Technologies: Java, Spring-Integration.

roles.title: Senior Java Developer Options Rock Project
notes:
OptionsRock FX Options Trading Interface
This was a fast front-end FX options trading system that used Calypso as a back-end platform for processing trade details. Gemfire was used as a persistence and data transport layer to communicating with Calypso.

Technologies: Java, Spring-Integration, Gemfire.

roles.title: Senior Java Developer Calypso Project
notes:
Calypso Custom Development
Calypso is used as the main front and back-end system for all FX, FX Options and Commodities trading. As such a number of customisations and extensions were developed including reporting functions, integration functions, pricing enhancements, risk reporting, etc.

Technologies: Java, Spring.

Calypso FX Options Pricing and Test Harness
In order to benchmark Calypso's pricing models against the bank own internal pricing model library, a comprehensive automated test harness was developed. The product coverage included FX Spot, Forward, Swaps, NDFs and FX Options including vanilla, barriers, Asian, digital. Pricing measures included all of the Greeks. Where discrepancies were found, the root cause had to be identified as being one of data-related, rounding, model differences or a bug. In most cases, remedial action was taken either by adding new configuration settings or by fixing the bug in Calypso. The test harness was written in core Java.

Technologies: Java, Spring.
